{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"47b004c5-2a8a-478c-b29f-7e65dd066994","content":"## What happened\n\n`DSA.Create()` now throws **`PlatformNotSupportedException`** on macOS. This is the culmination of a multi-release deprecation:\n\n1. **.NET 7** — DSA APIs were marked `[Obsolete]` (`SYSLIB0030`), producing compile-time warnings.\n2. **Later releases** — .NET on macOS dropped its OpenSSL dependency for crypto, relying on Apple's native frameworks instead. **Apple's Security framework does not support DSA**, so the managed wrapper has nothing to call.\n3. **.NET 11** — the runtime now throws at runtime on macOS rather than silently failing or requiring a side-loaded OpenSSL.\n\nWindows and Linux still work because Windows CNG and OpenSSL (on Linux) still expose DSA.\n\n## How to fix it\n\n**Option A — Use BouncyCastle (recommended for \"verify only\" legacy scenarios):**\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\n// Pure managed code — works on every OS, no native dependency.\nvar verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA256withDSA\");\nverifier.Init(forSigning: false, publicKey);   // DsaPublicKeyParameters\nverifier.BlockUpdate(data, 0, data.Length);\nbool valid = verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n```\n\n**Option B — Migrate away from DSA entirely.** If you control both sides, re-sign with **ECDSA** or **Ed25519** (supported natively on all platforms).\n\n**Option C (stop-gap) — Ship OpenSSL on macOS** via Homebrew (`brew install openssl`) and set `DOTNET_SYSTEM_SECURITY_CRYPTOGRAPHY_USEOPENSSL=1` (if supported by your runtime version). This is fragile and not recommended long-term.\n\n### TL;DR\n\nApple dropped DSA → .NET on macOS can no longer provide it → use BouncyCastle's managed DSA for cross-platform legacy signature verification.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"62f1973a-fb07-46f3-9eca-c5be34025038","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty, so this is a pure knowledge question. Let me provide a comprehensive answer.","outputTokens":560,"requestId":"6814:29E277:1107E46:155CD89:69FFE302"},"id":"73eba12f-395e-4315-a465-86cd98d4675d","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:44:50.029Z","parentId":"2f21e385-0b01-4a7e-8072-77dc3e8fc718"}
